Setting Parameters:

Preprocessing performed with Seurat and Scater, as mentioned in this example file: https://github.com/Rebecza/scRNA-seq/blob/main/preprocessing/20210105_DatasetVelocityPreparation_S2S_template.Rmd. Output to that Rmd file, will visualize multiple settings for PCs to use.

## Parameters ##
score_tresh = 0.0

## Storing results ##
anchor_set_location <- "../scrna/CMdiff_mon-EB-EHT_combined/rerun_v4/preprocess_R/20211025_ExpIntegration/seuset.anchors.rds"
workdir <- "../scrna/CMdiff_mon-EB-EHT_combined/rerun_v4/preprocess_R/"
# if regression is performed: this will already be included in the folder name
result_descript = "_ExpIntegration_AnchorEvaluation"
system(paste("mkdir -p ", workdir))
knitr::opts_knit$set(root.dir = normalizePath(workdir))

Loading the dataset

Normalized, scaled dataset with information on the highest variable genes (HVGs).

seuset.anchors <- readRDS(anchor_set_location)

Setting up results directory

dateoftoday <- gsub("-", "", as.character(Sys.Date()))
resultsdir <- paste(workdir, dateoftoday, result_descript, sep = "")
system(paste("mkdir -p ", resultsdir))
knitr::opts_knit$set(root.dir = normalizePath(resultsdir))

Results will be stored in: resultsdir

#seuset.anchors@object.list
orderedanchors <- seuset.anchors@anchors[order(seuset.anchors@anchors$score, decreasing = TRUE),]
orderedanchors <- orderedanchors[orderedanchors$score >= score_tresh,]
hist(seuset.anchors@anchors$score)

range(orderedanchors$score)
## [1] 0 1
#Obtain from the seurat.anchor object, the linked cell-names and scores attached
anchorsexplore <- setNames(data.frame(matrix(ncol = 3, nrow = 1)), c("cell1", "cell2", "score"))
anchorsexplore <- anchorsexplore[-1,]
anchorsexplore <- data.frame()
for (rowX in 1:length(rownames(orderedanchors))){
  cell1 <- seuset.anchors@object.list[[orderedanchors$dataset1[rowX]]]@meta.data[orderedanchors$cell1[rowX],]
  cell2 <- seuset.anchors@object.list[[orderedanchors$dataset2[rowX]]]@meta.data[orderedanchors$cell2[rowX],]
  cell1$combined_id2 <- paste(cell1$Method, cell1$Timepoint, cell1$Experiment, sep = "_")
  cell2$combined_id2 <- paste(cell2$Method, cell2$Timepoint, cell2$Experiment, sep = "_")
  
  scorevector <- c(cell1$combined_id2, cell2$combined_id2, orderedanchors$score[rowX])
  if (rowX == 1){
    anchorsexplore <- setNames(data.frame(matrix(ncol = 3, nrow = 1)), c("cell1", "cell2", "score"))
    anchorsexplore[1,] <- scorevector
    
  } else {
  anchorsexplore <- rbind(anchorsexplore, scorevector)
  }
}

anchorsunique <- anchorsexplore[!duplicated(anchorsexplore[,c("cell1", "cell2")]),]
